        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 22 at 9:14PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 914 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southeast of Briggsdale, or 27 miles east of Greeley, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Keota, Briggsdale and Buckingham.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
